<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1944-10-29T14:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1944-10-29T14:00:00-05:00" n="1076" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1076">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">711.94114 Supplies/10–2744:
                            Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of
                                    State</gloss> to the Chargé in the Soviet Union</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Kennan</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1944-10-29T15:00:00-04:00">October
                                    29, 1944—3 p.m.</date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>2558. ReEmbs 4120, October 27.<note n="14" xml:id="d1076fn1">See footnote
                                9, <ref target="#pg_1189">p. 1189</ref>.</note> American authorities
                            will accept all mail from Japan whether from American prisoners and
                            internees <pb facs="1202" n="1192" xml:id="pg_1192"/> in Japan or from
                            Japanese citizens to Japanese prisoners and internees in Western
                            Hemisphere. American authorities will also accept any relief supplies
                            sent from Japan for Japanese nationals in Allied custody<note n="15" xml:id="d1076fn2">Japanese goods received from the <hi rend="italic">Hakusan Maru</hi> for distribution in the United States reached
                                San Francisco near the end of November.</note> (see also Depts 2532,
                            October 26).</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Stettinius</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>